# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [1.2.0] - 2026-01-28

### Added
- **Enhanced Installer with Multiple Profiles**:
  - **Minimal Profile** (~2GB): Core system + Niri + basic tools
  - **Standard Profile** (~4GB): Minimal + dev tools + common apps
  - **Full Profile** (~6GB): Everything including Rust, Go, Java, all extras
- **Command-Line Options**:
  - `--help`: Display usage information and examples
  - `--dry-run`: Preview installation without making changes
  - `--skip-installed`: Skip packages that are already installed
  - `--profile`: Choose installation profile (minimal/standard/full)
- **Improved Error Handling**:
  - Automatic retry logic for network failures (3 attempts)
  - Better error messages and logging
  - Network connectivity retry with fallback
- **Progress Tracking**:
  - Percentage-based progress indicators
  - Step counting based on selected profile
  - Clearer installation status messages
- **Post-Installation Verification**:
  - Automatic verification of critical components
  - Profile-aware component checking
  - Service status verification (SDDM, Docker, etc.)
- **Documentation**:
  - New comprehensive `INSTALL.md` guide
  - Detailed profile comparisons
  - Installation examples and troubleshooting
  - Command-line flag documentation

### Changed
- Refactored installer for better modularity
- Improved logging system with graceful fallback for non-sudo dry-run
- Enhanced installation summary with profile-specific information
- Updated README.md with new installation options
- Better dry-run output formatting

### Improved
- Package installation now respects selected profile
- Better skip logic for already installed packages
- Clearer separation between minimal, standard, and full installations
- More informative installation completion messages

## [1.1.0] - 2026-01-28

### Added
- **Backup & Restore System**: Complete configuration management
  - `backup.sh` - Automated backup with git integration
  - `restore.sh` - Safe restoration with automatic backups
  - Archive creation for easy distribution
  - Git commit and push automation
  - Status reporting and backup tracking
- Safety features for restore operations:
  - Automatic backup before restore
  - Confirmation prompts
  - Timestamped safety backups in `~/.jarch-backups/`

### Changed
- Enhanced README with Backup & Restore section
- Added Quick Start guide
- Updated repository URL from fools-stack to Riain-stack
- Improved documentation structure

## [1.0.0] - 2026-01-28

### Added
- Complete Arch Linux coding distribution
- Automated installer with progress tracking and error handling
- SDDM display manager integration
- Niri Wayland compositor (Rust-based)
- Zsh shell with Starship prompt, autosuggestions, and vi-mode
- Alacritty GPU-accelerated terminal
- Neovim with LSP, treesitter, lazy.nvim, and Kanagawa theme
- Complete development environment:
  - Languages: Python, Node.js, Rust, Go, Java
  - Build tools: gcc, clang, cmake, make, ninja, valgrind, gdb, lldb
  - Version control: git, git-lfs, git-delta, lazygit
  - Containers: Docker, docker-compose
- Modern CLI tools: ripgrep, fd, bat, exa, btop, fzf, rofi
- Desktop applications: Firefox, Discord, Thunar
- Comprehensive dotfiles for all components
- Pre-install system checks
- Wayland and security enhancements
- MIT License
- Comprehensive documentation with FAQ and troubleshooting

### Changed
- Optimized installer with compressed commands and skip logic
- Enhanced Niri configuration
- Improved Zsh configuration
- Better error handling and logging throughout
- Detailed progress indicators
- Fixed ripgrep config file
- Fixed dotfiles structure and paths
- Corrected SCRIPT_DIR path resolution

### Fixed
- Packpath configuration
- Conform.nvim integration
- Zsh tmux condition
- Dotfiles directory structure
- Installation script paths

